content:
Service Cloud Chat uses cookies to improve functionality and accelerate processing times. By saving a user’s settings, cookies can enhance the user’s experience and the Chat performance.

Required editions: Enterprise, Unlimited, Performance, and Developer editions.

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026, and is in maintenance mode until then. You are recommended to migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

Service Cloud Chat collects two different types of cookies:

* Required: Strictly necessary for the website to work correctly.
* Functional: Used for analytics and performance.

The following table describes the Chat cookies collected by Salesforce:

COOKIE NAME	DURATION	COOKIE TYPE	DESCRIPTION
"liveagent_invite_rejected_"+this.buttonId	Session	Remembers the rules set by an admin to hide a chat invite button after a visitor accepts or rejects it.
liveagent_sid	Session	Captures a unique pseudonymous ID when a user requests a chat during an active session.
liveagent_chatted	Session	Captures where a user requests a chat during an active session.
liveagent_vc	1 year	Counts a user’s distinct browsing sessions on your website after closing previous sessions.
liveagent_oref	1 year	Captures how visitors arrive at your website from either search results or affiliate links.
liveagent_ptid	1 year	Links previous chats and transcripts from a single visitor.
title: Service Cloud Chat Cookie Policy
